trans-unit.source: The PositiveTimeSpanValidator is used to ensure a <xref:System.TimeSpan> object meets specific criteria.
trans-unit.target: PositiveTimeSpanValidator brukes til å sikre en <xref:System.TimeSpan>objektet oppfyller bestemte kriterier.</xref:System.TimeSpan>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Configuration.PositiveTimeSpanValidator.CanValidate%2A> method determines whether the object type being validated matches the expected type.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Configuration.PositiveTimeSpanValidator.CanValidate%2A>metoden bestemmer om objekttypen valideres samsvarer med den forventede typen.</xref:System.Configuration.PositiveTimeSpanValidator.CanValidate%2A>

trans-unit.source: The object being validated is passed as a parameter of the <xref:System.Configuration.PositiveTimeSpanValidator.Validate%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Objektet valideres sendes som en parameter for den <xref:System.Configuration.PositiveTimeSpanValidator.Validate%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Configuration.PositiveTimeSpanValidator.Validate%2A>

trans-unit.source: To pass validation, the object being validated must be a positive <xref:System.TimeSpan> value.
trans-unit.target: Valideringen skal være bestått objektet valideres må være et positivt <xref:System.TimeSpan>verdi.</xref:System.TimeSpan>
